modules.description: Provides functions to parse and manipulate indentation levels in text, including calculating leading spaces, adjusting indentation, and normalizing whitespace. Works with strings and integers to represent and modify indentation depth. Used to standardize code formatting in text processing pipelines and pretty-printing logic.

Removes leading whitespace from each line of a multi-line string and normalizes indentation. Processes strings containing line-separated content, preserving internal spacing within each line. Useful for formatting SQL queries, JSON templates, or code snippets embedded in OCaml programs.
